  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Title : 121 Personal Cash Aid Start and end dates: 01/06/2019 30/11/2020 (18 months) Pcode: P7987 Summary: BRC will support KRCS to build on the innovate finance in the IARP project and develop a blockchain 121 personal cash aid system using mobile technology - This project involves the development of mobile-enabled digital identity solutions which will improve beneficiary registration and subsequent aid delivery or provide secure digital identity profiles that can benefit refugees and IDPs. - The 121 cash programme funding is being used to pilot &amp; implement the full end-to-end system (including digital identity component; registering beneficiaries) Location: Isiolo county Kenya Beneficiaries: 1000 beneficiaries registered for the 121 blockchain system &amp; 750 beneficiaries receiving cash through the system Donor: GSMA &amp; matched funded by NLRC (RF) PNSs/Partners: Netherlands RC (510 NLRC data team) KRCS Budget: - Total funding from GSMA foundation - 286 870 - Total match funding - 143 570 (matched by NLRC) - Total project budget - 430 440 Current situation (Jan 2020): currently negotiating financial reporting requirements with GSMA and NLRC. Two milestones completed; work ongoing on system development (Netherlands RC working on this). Customer policy issues using digital identity for beneficiaries. KRCS working on looking at ministries and Central Bank and comms authority to give approval to use digital identity. Pilot will start in May 2020</narrative>
  </description>
